# Module Ownership

## Ownership map

| Developer | Frontend modules | API modules |
|-----------|------------------|-------------|
| Developer 1 | `modules/auth`, `modules/organization` | `api/modules/auth`, `api/modules/organization` |
| Developer 2 | `modules/assets`, `modules/allocation` | `api/modules/assets`, `api/modules/allocation` |
| Developer 3 | `modules/booking`, `modules/maintenance` | `api/modules/booking`, `api/modules/maintenance` |
| Developer 4 | `modules/dashboard`, `modules/audit`, `modules/reports`, `modules/notifications` | `api/modules/audit`, `api/modules/reports`, `api/modules/notifications` |

Paths are under `src/app/`.

## Rules

- Developers work only inside owned folders.
- Shared folders (`src/app/shared/`), app routing, providers, guards, root configuration, and package files are protected.
- One designated integrator should approve changes to shared, app routing, providers, root configuration, and package files.
- Cursor must ask which developer/module is active if the requested task does not clearly identify ownership.
- Cursor must not modify files belonging to another developer.
